 healing, liberal Protestants became pioneers three times over: in the struggle against the cultural and medical pathologizing of homosexuality; in the critique of Christian missionary triumphalism; and in the diffusion of an ever-more ubiquitous anthropology of "body, mind, and spirit." At a time when the political and anthropological significance of Christianity is being hotly debated, Spirits of Protestantism forcefully argues for a reconsideration of the historical legacies and cultural effects of liberal Protestantism, even for the anthropology of religion itself.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Mai 2023) 0aHealingxReligious aspectsxProtestant churches. 0aLiberalism (Religion) - North America - History. 0aLiberalism (Religion) -- North America -- History. 0aLiberalism (Religion)zNorth AmericaxHistory. 0aProtestant churches -- North America -- History. 0aProtestant churcheszNorth AmericaxHistory. 0aProtestantism -- North America -- History. 0aProtestantismzNorth AmericaxHistory. 7aRELIGION / Christianity / General.2bisacsh  a20th century anthropology.  a20th century christianity.  a20th century protestants.  aanthropology and christianity.  acanada and religion.  achristian history.  achristian missionary.  achristian salvation theory.  achristian students.  achristianity and protestants.  aethnography and religion.  aliberal christianity.  aliberal protestantism.  aliberal protestants.  amedical missionaries.  amedicine and christianity.  amedicine and religion.  areligious history.  areligious studies students.  ascience and religion.  asecularism and religion.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of California Press Backlist Package 2000-2013z97831106904220 cprintz978052024428340uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/978052095044340uhttps://w